dct_title_s: Plate-V: Distribution of shellfish resources in relation to the New Jersey Intracoastal Waterway, Longport to Cape May
dct_description_sm: Image is from a copy of the original on Mylar.

Prepared by the U.S. Department of the Interior, Fish and Wildlife Service, Bureau of Sport Fisheries and Wildlife, Boston, Massachusetts, based on information supplied by the Division of Shell Fisheries, Department of Conservation and Economic Development, Trenton, New Jersey.
Shellfish resources charted on the map include oysters, hard clams, and soft clams.

Note A: Navigation regulations are published in Chapter 2. Coast Pilot 2, or subsequent yearly supplements and weekly Notices to Mariners. Copies of the regulations may be obtained at the office of the District Engineer, Corps of Engineers in New York. Refer to section numbers shown with area designation.
